object.text: Specifies the object type which is 'subscription'.

created.text: Unix timestamp when the object was created.

currency.text: Currency used in the transaction, here it is 'usd'.

current_period_end.text: Unix timestamp for the end of the current billing period.

current_period_start.text: Unix timestamp for the start of the current billing period.

latest_invoice.text: Identifier of the latest invoice object.

metadata.text: A set of key-value pairs that can be attached to the object. This can be useful for storing additional, flexible metadata on the object. Here we have keys like 'netsuite_CF_funnel_id' and 'netsuite_CF_funnel_name'.

plan.text: The plan the subscription is subscribed to. It contains fields like id, object, active, amount, currency, interval, livemode, and usage_type.

start_date.text: Unix timestamp when the subscription started.

status.text: Current status of the subscription ('trialing', 'active', etc.).

trial_end.text: Unix timestamp when the trial period ends.

trial_start.text: Unix timestamp when the trial period starts.
